BP will be able to tap the Oil Spill Liability Trust Fund, which was
established after the Exxon Valdez (XOM) oil spill. The fund collects 8 cents
from the industry for every barrel of oil produced or imported to the U.S.
Currently this fund has about $1.6 billion available to cover damages suffered
by coastal residents, fishermen and other affected businesses.
