and Mid-Continent/Gulf States.

The company has no exposure to deep drilling wells in the Gulf and could
possibly benefit from BP's tragic accident.

The geographic region MDU operates in has had extensive new capital investment
in NG shale well exploration & development. These new wells will require the NG
gathering, storage and transportation services that MDU provides. With a
forward PE around 12 and a dividend that yields 3%, MDU represents a good GARP
stock investment.

