Date:5/6/2010 1:01:31 AM
From:Spekulatius
re BLK - I don't think it's fair to compare BLK to traditional asset managers
like BEN, TROW etc. I claim so because BLK does mostly low cost index funds/ETF
that charge fees of <0.2% annually while TROW can charge >0.8% typically for
and actively managed fund. So to achieve the same revenue, BLK needs to have
>4X the amount of AUM compared to their competitors. So you cannot compare
BLK's market cap / AUM ratio directly.

I do like how BLK position themselves. The Barclays Ishares buy was not cheap
but it's a great operation. I think a lot of money in managed accounts and
retirement account and such will migrate to ETF, especially now with trades
getting cheaper and cheaper (Fidelity & Vanguard offer free trading for their
ETF's).
